         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Hartfield Grove, ¶ Hartfield, ¶ Tunbridge Wells. ¶ July 30 ¶ 1890...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">90.07.30</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Elizabeth Gore</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M108b, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: center; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="form%20text" style="color: #2f5496; font-family: Times; ">Hartfield Grove,</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: center; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="form%20text" style="color: #2f5496; font-family: Times; ">Hartfield,</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: center; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="form%20text" style="color: #2f5496; font-family: Times; ">Tunbridge Wells.</seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">July 30</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">1890</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Baron Ferdinand von Müller</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Your charming gift of Algae<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See E. Gore to M, 8 April 1890.</p>
               </note> was forwarded to me here, where we are staying for the summer, and I know not how to express my thanks for your kindness. So many novelties &amp; such beautiful specimens! They are indeed a splendid addition to my collection!</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have also to thank you for many, forwarded to me by Prof Agardh, when distributing his duplicates. I wish our English Societies were as liberal as you are — it is a pity so many duplicates that would be such a treasure to collectors, are locked up to spoil in museums. It seems to me the study of Algology, so appropriate to our Islands, is declining in this country, probably because not encouraged. There cannot be a more attractive branch of Natural History. I mean to leave my collection to our Brighton Museum.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>This is a very pretty part of Sussex — it is called Ashdown Forest "lucus a non lucendo",<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">i.e. a non sequitur.</p>
               </note> as the trees have long ago been cut down; but the very large heath, studded with fine Hollies and Thorns, is very attractive, especially now that the heath is in blossom. About 3 miles distant, is Lord De la Warre's place, Buckhurst, where the beech trees &amp; oak are splendid &amp; the red deer look so picturesque in the glades.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The American sheoaks do remarkably well in the peaty soil here, &amp; in this place was one <name key="Rhododendron">Rhododendron</name> that measured 103 feet round &amp; was one blaze of blossom! The <name key="Kalmia">Kalmia</name>s &amp; <name key="Azalea">Azalea</name>s were also lovely. We have had a cold &amp; changeable summer and the hay is only just got in.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I did not write so soon as I could have wished, on the receipt of your delightful parcel, as my sister &amp; I were both laid up with severe colds. It would be an honour as well as a pleasure, to send specimens in return, &amp; when I go back to my home at Brighton in Sept, I shall look over my collection and see whether there is anything worthy of your acceptance.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">In the mean time</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Believe me to remain</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>your's gratefully</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Elizabeth E Gore</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">How beautiful are <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>"<name key="Glaphyrymenia%20pustulosa">Glaphyrymenia pustulosa</name>" — Cryptomenia<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Cryptonemia wilsonii</seg>?</p>
               </note> Wilsoni <name key="Wrangelia%20ballioides">Wrangelia ballioides</name> — <name key="Horea%20Wilsoni">Horea Wilsoni</name> &amp; that Queen of Seaweeds, "<name key="Claudea%20elegans">Claudea elegans</name>"!</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
